cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.SI, cs.CL

This paper deals with building compliance classifiers for CPAP therapy, which involves analyzing patient data to predict their adherence to the treatment. This falls under the category of computational methods for healthcare (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of clinical analytical tools to support prediction, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper involves analyzing patient data to identify relevant factors for compliance, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.SI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
